node.text:
Aaye Kuch Abr is a poem written by Urdu poet Faiz Ahmad Faiz. It was written during Faiz's life of isolation and separation, while he was lodged in Hyderabad Central Jail during the Rawalpindi conspiracy case. This was also the time when he was away from his wife and two daughters. 

The literal translation of the first stanza reads something like this and it's beautiful to say the least! 

'While counting the times this world tormented me; the thought of you today
was beyond all reckoning'. 

In 2011, this ghazal was performed 
by none other than Mehdi Hassan

Later, It was sung by Atif Aslam during Coke Studio season 12
